1
00:00:06,148 --> 00:00:08,671
Gurudev says 
through his god-brothers
 

2
00:00:08,671 --> 00:00:12,531
he understood the glories
of Guru Mahārāj.

3
00:00:12,531 --> 00:00:17,031
Through Guru Mahārāj we understood
how exalted Śrīla Prabhupād was.

4
00:00:17,051 --> 00:00:18,951
And I can tell you 
the same way,

5
00:00:18,951 --> 00:00:21,889
“You really want to understand
how great Śrīla Gurudev is,

6
00:00:21,889 --> 00:00:25,515
Śrīla Bhakti Sundar Govinda 
Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj,

7
00:00:25,515 --> 00:00:28,256
then you can come 
and talk to me about it,

8
00:00:28,256 --> 00:00:30,855
and I’ll tell you 
what I know about him”,

9
00:00:30,855 --> 00:00:34,097
if you’re interested 
in that kind of thing.

10
00:00:34,380 --> 00:00:39,130
[Srila B. S. Govinda Maharaj’s 
Ecstatic Interior]

11
00:00:39,426 --> 00:00:42,526
But if you’re interested
in the Ten Commandments,

12
00:00:42,536 --> 00:00:45,732
and what you think
is chiseled in stone,

13
00:00:45,732 --> 00:00:50,036
in some imaginary 
Govinda Mahārāj,

14
00:00:50,451 --> 00:00:53,035
the Govinda Mahārāj
of your imagination—

15
00:00:53,035 --> 00:00:55,612
you want to offer 
the mind’s bananas

16
00:00:55,612 --> 00:00:58,612
to the Govinda Mahārāj 
of your imagination;

17
00:00:58,612 --> 00:01:00,162
then as Guru Mahārāj 
would say,
 

18
00:01:00,162 --> 00:01:04,082
“Let them dance 
with their foolish tendency!”

19
00:01:04,082 --> 00:01:06,057
I won’t waste 
my time with that.

20
00:01:06,607 --> 00:01:08,413
But if people 
want to understand

21
00:01:08,413 --> 00:01:13,313
something about
Śrīla Gurudev’s ecstatic interior …

22
00:01:13,313 --> 00:01:16,555
We have the kokil here.

23
00:01:16,555 --> 00:01:19,555
Why does the kokil 
remind me of him?

24
00:01:19,555 --> 00:01:22,113
We were in Navadvīp,
we heard the kokils.

25
00:01:22,113 --> 00:01:26,333
[Whistles like a bird]

26
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:27,524
Up, up, up …
He said,

27
00:01:27,524 --> 00:01:32,354
“Oh, it’s two males competing 
for the affection of the female.”

28
00:01:33,344 --> 00:01:34,344
So, they were going like,

29
00:01:34,344 --> 00:01:36,353
—Listen, how sweet I can do that!
—No, I can do it sweeter!

30
00:01:36,353 --> 00:01:39,403
—Sweeter!—Sweeter!—Sweeter!
—Sweeter! —Sweeter!

31
00:01:42,966 --> 00:01:49,722
And then … And I’m thinking,
“Oh, Goswāmīs …”, like:

32
00:01:49,722 --> 00:01:56,988
kujat-kokila-hamsa-sarasa-ganakirne mayurakule
[Ṣaḍ-gosvāmy-aṣṭakam]

33
00:01:56,988 --> 00:01:59,258
of Śrīnivās Āchārya.

34
00:01:59,258 --> 00:02:02,552
They’re always talking 
about the kokil, and we know

35
00:02:02,552 --> 00:02:06,005
it’s a parakīya symbol—

36
00:02:06,005 --> 00:02:11,405
the kokil lays their eggs 
in another bird’s nest,

37
00:02:11,405 --> 00:02:15,513
and other bird raises them 
thinking they are their own.

38
00:02:15,513 --> 00:02:18,684
It’s a symbol of parakīya.

39
00:02:18,684 --> 00:02:23,037
Anyway, and then Gurudev says …
He quotes this verse:

40
00:02:23,037 --> 00:02:33,154
jaiminir iti jaiminir iti jalpati sa-viṣādam
kurvati kila kokila-kula ujjvala-kala-nādam
[Stavamala]

41
00:02:33,154 --> 00:02:35,352
And then he says,

42
00:02:35,352 --> 00:02:44,722
“Rādhārāṇī’s jap, She’s going, 
‘Jaimini, Jaimini, Jaimini …’”

43
00:02:44,722 --> 00:02:49,411
Why is She chanting
the name of Jaimini?

44
00:02:50,084 --> 00:02:55,489
Because generally we know 
the sound of the kokil

45
00:02:55,489 --> 00:02:58,679
is like liquid sweetness.

46
00:02:58,679 --> 00:03:00,532
That …
(Thank you!)

47
00:03:02,889 --> 00:03:04,987
Liquid sweetness.

48
00:03:04,987 --> 00:03:08,597
And it’s reminiscent
of the voice of Kṛṣṇa.

49
00:03:08,597 --> 00:03:13,649
Sometimes it’s taken … 
Rādhārānī’s voice is compared to a kokil.

50
00:03:13,649 --> 00:03:17,147
It’s just … liquid sweetness
is the sound of the kokil.

51
00:03:17,147 --> 00:03:19,500
And what did they do?

52
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:22,510
It gets sweeter and sweeter,
and sweeter …

53
00:03:22,510 --> 00:03:25,365
It just keeps 
getting sweeter.

54
00:03:25,365 --> 00:03:29,379
So you would think
like the neophytes,

55
00:03:29,379 --> 00:03:34,669
the nectar-hounds, 
who want sweet things

56
00:03:34,669 --> 00:03:39,809
that hearing the kokil 
should make you feel happy.

57
00:03:39,829 --> 00:03:45,679
But Rādhārānī is going, “Jaimini,
Jaimini, Jaimini, Jaimini, Jaimini!”

58
00:03:45,679 --> 00:03:54,262
In a very desperate way, fervently 
She’s jap chanting, “Jaimini!”

59
00:03:54,262 --> 00:04:00,070
Why? Because, Gurudev explained,
it is their tradition

60
00:04:00,070 --> 00:04:04,043
that the girls of Vṛndāvan
and everybody in Vṛndāvan that …

61
00:04:04,043 --> 00:04:08,623
it is said that when
there is thunder and lightning

62
00:04:08,623 --> 00:04:12,870
that to protect yourself 
from being struck by lightning

63
00:04:12,870 --> 00:04:15,902
you should take 
the name of Jaimini Ṛṣi.

64
00:04:15,902 --> 00:04:19,131
So, when it’s like [lightning]
in the sky, you go, “Jaimini, Jaimini!”,

65
00:04:19,131 --> 00:04:21,603
and you won’t get struck 
by lightning.

66
00:04:21,603 --> 00:04:25,528
So everybody chants 
the name of Jaimini Ṛṣi.

67
00:04:25,935 --> 00:04:29,993
But why is Rādhārānī chanting 
his name?

68
00:04:30,107 --> 00:04:39,767
Because in viraha-bhāv, 
separation …

69
00:04:40,293 --> 00:04:42,861
Like Dās Goswāmī:

70
00:04:42,861 --> 00:04:47,847
Govardhan is the python 
coming to swallow him,

71
00:04:47,847 --> 00:04:51,827
Rādhā-kunda is the tiger’s 
gaping jaws.

72
00:04:51,827 --> 00:04:57,765
In separation from Kṛṣṇa
the sweet sound of the kokil

73
00:04:57,765 --> 00:05:00,406
that’s reminiscent 
of the voice of Kṛṣṇa

74
00:05:00,406 --> 00:05:05,096
is like lightning 
striking Her heart.

75
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:09,739
That’s why She’s going,
“Jaimini, Jaimini …”—

76
00:05:09,739 --> 00:05:14,339
“Save Me from being struck 
by the lightning of the sweetness

77
00:05:14,339 --> 00:05:20,959
of the voice of the kokil
that’s breaking My heart!”

78
00:05:23,751 --> 00:05:26,348
That is Śrīla Bhakti 
[Sundar Govinda Dev-Goswami Mahārāj]

79
00:05:26,348 --> 00:05:27,428
that is like just

80
00:05:27,428 --> 00:05:33,716
Śrīla Bhakti Sundar Govinda Dev-Goswami Mahārāj 
between snacks.

81
00:05:33,716 --> 00:05:40,011
But you saw the snack 
and want to talk about the snack.

82
00:05:40,011 --> 00:05:43,130
That’s what 
I find disappointing.

83
00:05:43,130 --> 00:05:45,254
And a snack is OK.

84
00:05:45,254 --> 00:05:48,354
And all that is OK
and fine, and well, and good.

85
00:05:48,354 --> 00:05:52,484
But to miss this other thing,
which is the actual wealth

86
00:05:52,484 --> 00:05:57,269
of Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh, 
is worrisome.

87
00:05:57,729 --> 00:05:59,026
And I’m not going 
to let up,

88
00:05:59,026 --> 00:06:02,486
I’m going to hold your feet 
to the fire, I’m sorry!

89
00:06:02,706 --> 00:06:05,144
Steve Jobs 
made his employees cry,

90
00:06:05,144 --> 00:06:08,944
and that’s why you’ve got 
an iPhone in your pocket.

91
00:06:09,294 --> 00:06:11,274
But that’s not 
how this works.

92
00:06:11,274 --> 00:06:14,353
There’re little girls 
in the spiritual world 
 

93
00:06:14,353 --> 00:06:19,043
who are crying, 
and I care about them.

94
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:23,756
And they are crying 
for another reason.

95
00:06:23,933 --> 00:06:30,270
And that Guru Mahārāj tells
Rūpa Goswāmī says in his śloka.

96
00:06:32,929 --> 00:06:38,337
Rādhārānī, usually She is crying,
but stops after a while

97
00:06:38,337 --> 00:06:40,607
in separation.

98
00:06:40,607 --> 00:06:44,457
But this time 
She cannot stop crying,

99
00:06:44,457 --> 00:06:48,777
and the guru-varga of Vṛndāvan
are upset.

100
00:06:48,777 --> 00:06:57,082
Who are the guru-varga?
Nanda, Yaśhodā, Paurṇamāsī, others.

101
00:06:57,082 --> 00:07:02,812
And everyone is afraid Rādhārānī 
is going to leave the world.

102
00:07:02,827 --> 00:07:07,993
The tenth stage of separation
is death.

103
00:07:08,363 --> 00:07:09,938
So …

104
00:07:13,338 --> 00:07:15,678
they’re wondering 
what to do.

105
00:07:15,678 --> 00:07:24,930
And Chandrāvalī, Her chief competitor, 
she comes and admits

106
00:07:24,930 --> 00:07:29,239
that Rādhārānī is superior,
and says,

107
00:07:29,239 --> 00:07:34,337
“Actually, if You do this,
if You commit suicide, then Kṛṣṇa …

108
00:07:34,344 --> 00:07:37,878
then none of us have any hope 
of ever seeing Him again.

109
00:07:37,878 --> 00:07:41,718
We know, You have the power
to bring Him back here.

110
00:07:41,718 --> 00:07:43,711
I don’t have it, 
they don’t have it.

111
00:07:43,711 --> 00:07:46,931
But You do, 
You alone have that power.

112
00:07:46,931 --> 00:07:50,299
And if we lose You, even
I compete with You all the time,

113
00:07:50,299 --> 00:07:53,529
if we lose You,
we’ve lost everything.

114
00:07:53,529 --> 00:07:55,470
So I admit it—
You are superior,

115
00:07:55,470 --> 00:08:02,115
and I’m begging You
at Your lotus feet, ‘Don’t do this!’”

116
00:08:02,115 --> 00:08:10,082
And then, we’re told, mysteriously 
Śrīmatī Rādhārānī stops crying

117
00:08:10,082 --> 00:08:14,906
and then all of Her tears spring out 
of the eyes of Her servitors.

118
00:08:14,906 --> 00:08:20,759
Now they’re all crying incessantly,
and She’s happy.

119
00:08:21,002 --> 00:08:23,862
And that’s what 
this is all about.

120
00:08:23,862 --> 00:08:29,369
It’s time for all of us … 
Stop making Govinda Mahārāj cry.

121
00:08:29,369 --> 00:08:31,749
Let him be happy.

122
00:08:31,749 --> 00:08:36,409
And let all of his tears be transferred,
you’ve got to start crying.

123
00:08:36,411 --> 00:08:38,713
That’s my message to you

124
00:08:38,713 --> 00:08:43,374
as the sincere followers and disciples
of Śrīla Govinda Mahāhāraj

125
00:08:43,374 --> 00:08:47,349
it’s time for you 
to shed tears.

126
00:08:47,349 --> 00:08:50,552
Jay Om Viṣṇupād
Śrīla Bhakti Sundar Govinda 
Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj

127
00:08:50,552 --> 00:08:53,342
Avirbhāv Maha-Mahotsav Tithi ki!
[Devotees]: “Jay!”

128
00:08:53,342 --> 00:08:57,642
Śrīla Bhakti Rakṣak Śrīdhar Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj ki!
[Devotees]: “Jay!”

